The Navigate360 (&#8220;P3&#8221;) data breach seems to finally be getting some attention in Canada. Nicole O&#8217;Reilly reports: Hamilton police say they’ve been made aware that a cybersecurity incident earlier this year affecting a U.S.-based online platform includes a breach of Crime Stoppers of Hamilton data. The P3 platform, owned by Navigate360, is under contract with...<img alt="" height="0" src="https://databreaches.net/wp-content/plugins/wp-piwik/proxy/matomo.php?idsite=11&amp;rec=1&amp;url=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2F2026%2F06%2F18%2Fcybersecurity-breach-includes-crime-stoppers-of-hamilton-data%2F%3Fpk_campaign%3Dfeed%26pk_kwd%3Dcybersecurity-breach-includes-crime-stoppers-of-hamilton-data&amp;action_name=Cybersecurity%20breach%20includes%20Crime%20Stoppers%20of%20Hamilton%20data&amp;urlref=https%3A%2F%2Fdatabreaches.net%2Ffeed%2F" style="border: 0; width: 0; height: 0;" width="0" />
<p><a href="https://databreaches.net/2026/06/18/cybersecurity-breach-includes-crime-stoppers-of-hamilton-data/?pk_campaign=feed&#038;pk_kwd=cybersecurity-breach-includes-crime-stoppers-of-hamilton-data">Source</a></p>

